ğŸ”¹ Storing passwords in plain text is not a good idea because anyone with internal access can see them.
 
ğŸ”¹ Storing password hashes directly is not sufficient because it is pruned to precomputation attacks, such as rainbow tables. 
 
ğŸ”¹ To mitigate precomputation attacks, we salt the passwords. 

